The Case Deferment function is intended to capture elapsed time for cases that cannot move forward in IDES due to external delays lasting a minimum of 30 days. Examples of such cases include but are not limited to: pending Dual Action; approved leave/TAD/TDY; additional medical treatment is needed; Service member is placed on Continuation on Active Duty (COAD), Continuation on Active Reserve (COAR), Permanent Limited Duty (PLD) or Limited Assignment Status (LAS) for less than one year. This function is not intended to be used when cases are awaiting correction to the case file (e.g. return to an earlier step in the process, additional diagnostic exam, missing signature) to continue processing as those should be captured using the Corrective Action function in VTA. Only PEBLOs, PEB Admins, DoD Support Team and Admins may initiate, update or close deferment actions.
